tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows dyslipidemia with elevated total and LDL cholesterol and low HDL cholesterol, increasing cardiovascular risk. HbA1c is below normal, possibly reflecting hypoglycemia or recent changes in glucose metabolism, though current glucose is normal. Creatinine is slightly low but not clinically significant. Other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend further cardiovascular risk assessment and review of glycemic control.
